<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1474,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1582,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Frons with black median stripe medially; mesonotum black with white hairs; halter yellow completely; scutellum bicolored, black basally, posterior margin yellow; epandrium with single apicolateral process; gonocoxites fused medially, medially with sclerotized, black, sickle shaped processes [gonostyli].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1474,2003]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[356,460,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Holotype</typeStatus>
male (
<figureCitation box="[548,617,1690,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
b). Lengths. Body: 
<quantity box="[853,948,1691,1715]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
; wing: 
<quantity box="[1041,1135,1691,1715]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. Head. Subglobular; eyes dichoptic, width at vertex 1.5 times distance between lateral ocelli; occiput and vertex black; ocellar triangle black; frons slightly depressed medially, black just below middle ocellus at level of upper eye margin (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1290,1762,1787]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
f), extending downward as narrow stripe; face and oral margin yellow; antennae brown, scape minute, pedicel cylindrical, slightly longer than wide, first flagellomere ellipsoid, length about two times greatest width, second flagellomere cylindrical, length one-half of first flagellomere, with minute apical style; proboscis brown, length slightly shorter (0.8 x) than head height, labrum sclerotized, stiff, pointed apically, equal to proboscis in length (
<figureCitation box="[1268,1346,1906,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
a, b, c). Thorax. Pronotum black; mesonotum black (
<figureCitation box="[649,712,1942,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
e), with minute white hairs, postpronotal lobe and postalar callus yellow, yellow lateral margin from postpronotal lobe to postalar callus interrupted by broad black stripe at wing base; scutellum bicolored, black basally, posterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[921,987,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
e); pleura (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1196,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
a, b, c) black except yellow on following: propleuron completely, small spot posteromedially on anepisternum, anterior margin of anepisternum, upper margin of katepisternum, katepimeron, and upper margin of anepimeron; halter stem and knob yellowish white. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[419,485,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
c). Coxae brown; femora brown except apices yellow; tibiae brownish yellow; two basal tarsal segments yellow, remainder yellowish brown; claws black. Wing. Hyaline, Sc, Rs basally, vein separating basal cells and anal vein white to translucent; costal, radial, and medial veins brown; costa ends slightly beyond end of R4+5; vein Sc incomplete, ending at level about equal to origin of vein R2+3; vein R2+3 end in wing margin equidistance from vein R1 and R4+5; cell dm open, without crossvein closing it apically; vein M1+2 one half length of fork point to margin of wing; length of cell br 1.5 times that of cell bm, anal cell narrowly open at wing margin, width subequal to r-m crossvein; fringe of hair on posterior margin of wing minute. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1403,481,506]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
d). Tergites dark brown, lateral margins yellow, anterior margin of first tergite and posterior margin of all tergites narrowly yellow; sternites almost all brown, posterior margins of all sternites yellow; hypopygium dark brown except outer margin of epandrium narrowly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[748,813,589,614]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male and female: a. female paratype lateral view; b. male holotype; c. paratype male in alcohol; d. male abdomen dorsal view; e. male mesonotum dorsal view; f. male head dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582012/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
c). Male genitalia. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1239,589,614]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[170,1391,194,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male genitalia: a. epandrium dorsal view; b. gonocoxites ventral view; c. gonocoxites dorsal view; d. phallic complex, lateral view. mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
d) subquadrate in dorsal view, apicolaterally with short process [pseudosurstylus], cercus triangular, membranous, inner margin slightly sclerotized; Gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[533,610,661,686]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[170,1391,194,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male genitalia: a. epandrium dorsal view; b. gonocoxites ventral view; c. gonocoxites dorsal view; d. phallic complex, lateral view. mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
b, c) fused medially, oval in lateral view, subquadrate in ventral view, with a large pointed process apicolaterally, medioventrally with short process having long and whitish bristly hairs (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[170,1391,194,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male genitalia: a. epandrium dorsal view; b. gonocoxites ventral view; c. gonocoxites dorsal view; d. phallic complex, lateral view. mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
b), medially with sclerotized, black, sickle shaped processes [gonostyli] (
<figureCitation box="[995,1065,733,758]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[170,1391,194,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male genitalia: a. epandrium dorsal view; b. gonocoxites ventral view; c. gonocoxites dorsal view; d. phallic complex, lateral view. mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
c); in lateral view basal aedeagal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[270,338,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[170,1391,194,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrtosia baccadomus sp. nov., male genitalia: a. epandrium dorsal view; b. gonocoxites ventral view; c. gonocoxites dorsal view; d. phallic complex, lateral view. mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
a) large, inverted T-shaped, slightly longer than gonocoxal apodemes, anteriorly pointed; lateral aedeagal apodemes triangular, aedeagal bulb large, oval with small finger-shaped process laterally, narrowing as very long aedeagus.
</paragraph>
