<emphasis bold="true" box="[345,359,1981,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">b</emphasis>
. Joladak mountainous rangeland (
<taxonomicName box="[712,891,1981,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispermatheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[712,891,1981,2003]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">C. bispermatheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[899,980,1981,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[899,980,1981,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1003,1014,1981,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">c</emphasis>
. Loshan, rocky hills (
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1398,1981,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccadomus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1241,1398,1981,2003]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">C. baccadomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" box="[199,1046,877,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,877,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Female</emphasis>
. similar to males but larger in size. Female genitalia. Not dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="235" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,913,938]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is composed of two Latin words: 
<emphasis box="[1058,1125,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">bacca</emphasis>
[= olive berry] + 
<emphasis box="[1330,1403,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">domus</emphasis>
[= home] and refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[428,476,950,974]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
specimens being collected from Loshan (
<collectingRegion box="[956,1150,949,974]" country="Iran" name="Qazvin" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Qazvin province</collectingRegion>
), the olive growing area. The name is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="235" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1021,1046]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Distribution.</emphasis>
At the present time this species is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[943,992,1022,1045]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The city of Loshan in 
<collectingRegion box="[1250,1436,1021,1046]" country="Iran" name="Qazvin" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Qazvin province</collectingRegion>
(
<typeStatus box="[158,208,1058,1082]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
locality) has a Mediterranean climate, covered with rocky and sandy hills and includes numerous olive gardens (
<figureCitation box="[253,320,1093,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1951,1973]" captionTargetBox="[411,1169,193,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[411,1169,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. The different localities of Qazvin province from where type material were collected a. Nodahak rangeland (C. zieglerii sp. nov.), b. Joladak mountainous rangeland (C. bispermatheca sp. nov.), c. Loshan, rocky hills (C. baccadomus sp. nov.)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/582014/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
c). Specimens were swept from an unidentified composite plant blooming with yellow flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1129,1154]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[326,573,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccadomus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[326,573,1129,1153]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Cyrtosia baccadomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,678,1129,1154]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[584,678,1129,1154]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished from the congeners in 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1192,1130,1153]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Iran</collectingCountry>
by the colors of the scutellum, frons and halter. This species is separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[825,943,1166,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[825,943,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bicolorous scutellum that is basally brown and marginally yellow (completely black in 
<taxonomicName box="[727,842,1202,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[727,842,1202,1225]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having a black median stripe on the frons (a small spot on frons in 
<taxonomicName box="[401,516,1238,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[401,516,1238,1261]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species is separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[933,1131,1237,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispermatheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[933,1131,1237,1261]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. bispermatheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1138,1228,1237,1262]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1138,1228,1237,1262]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the completely yellow halter knob (in 
<taxonomicName box="[409,608,1273,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispermatheca">
<emphasis box="[409,608,1273,1297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. bispermatheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the halter knob has a large brown spot) and from 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1302,1273,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zieglerii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1176,1302,1273,1297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. zieglerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1400,1273,1298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1309,1400,1273,1298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the yellow frons with a black stripe medially (mostly black in 
<taxonomicName box="[848,973,1309,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zieglerii">
<emphasis box="[848,973,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. zieglerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and having a single apicolateral process on the epandrium (paired processes on the epandrium in 
<taxonomicName box="[786,911,1345,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zieglerii">
<emphasis box="[786,911,1345,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. zieglerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
In both 
<taxonomicName box="[284,381,1382,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,381,1382,1405]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Cyrtosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys, the key to Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[704,835,1381,1406]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" refString="Engel, O. (1933) Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. IV (3). Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 97 - 144." type="journal article" year="1933">Engel 1933</bibRefCitation>
) and to Mediterranean species (
<bibRefCitation author="Seguy" box="[1189,1327,1382,1406]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" refString="Seguy, E. (1949) Un Cyrtosia nouveau et synopsis des especes mediterraneennes (Dipt. Bombyliidae). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, 16, 83 - 85." type="journal article" year="1949">Séguy 1949</bibRefCitation>
), our new species runs to 
<taxonomicName box="[326,477,1418,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[326,477,1418,1441]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it easily separated by the color of the frons. Our new species has a yellow frons with a black stripe medially, but in 
<taxonomicName box="[545,694,1454,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[545,694,1454,1477]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the frons is almost all black except narrowly yellow at the base of the antennae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">
<bibRefCitation author="Efflatoun" box="[199,385,1525,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" refString="Efflatoun, H. C. (1945) A monograph of Egyptian Diptera. Part VI. Family Bombyliidae. Section I: Subfamily Bombyliidae Homeophthalmae. Bulletin de la Societe Fouad I er d'Entomologie, 29, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1945">Efflatoun (1945)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to Egyptian species of 
<taxonomicName box="[817,914,1526,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,914,1526,1549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Cyrtosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on his key, 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1299,1525,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccadomus">
<emphasis box="[1127,1299,1525,1549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. baccadomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezzi, 1925" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,401,1561,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubila">
<emphasis box="[151,257,1561,1585]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">C. nubila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi" box="[266,401,1561,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" refString="Bezzi, M. (1925) Quelques notes sur les bombyliides (Dipt.) d'Egypte, avec description d'especes nouvelles. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique d'Egypte, 8, 159 - 242." type="journal article" year="1925">Bezzi, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but the color of frons is quite different in the two species so they are easily distinguished. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,394,1597,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccadomus">
<emphasis box="[151,394,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="235">Cyrtosia baccadomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a black stripe on the yellow frons separates it from the Egyptian species with an almost all black frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
